{
  "texts": [
    "The weights are adjusted iteratively until the network's output matches the desired output for a given input.",
    "This process allows the neural network to learn from the data and improve its performance over time [49,50].",
    "In this paper, the task of the DNN model is to classify CAF maps as either spoofed or clean.",
    "This classification is performed in a probabilistic manner, yielding probabilities for both hypotheses.",
    "The input for the NNs is derived from the sub-image obtained by sliding across the delay/Doppler grid of the CAF evaluation."
  ]
}